<div class="floating-shape shape1"></div>
<div class="floating-shape shape2"></div>
<div class="floating-shape shape3"></div>

<div class="guide-container">
    <h1 class="guide-title">🌟 API Error Guide</h1>
    <p>Learn to quickly identify, understand, and fix common API responses and errors.</p>

    <div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-200">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill"></i>
            <h5>200 OK</h5>
            <p>Request successful. The server returned the expected data.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Always verify payload matches your expected structure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-400">
            <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle-fill"></i>
            <h5>400 Bad Request</h5>
            <p>Malformed request or missing parameters.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Check headers, payloads, and query parameters carefully.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-404">
            <i class="bi bi-x-circle-fill"></i>
            <h5>404 Not Found</h5>
            <p>The requested resource does not exist.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Confirm URL, endpoint, and resource ID.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-500">
            <i class="bi bi-exclamation-octagon-fill"></i>
            <h5>500 Internal Server Error</h5>
            <p>Server encountered an unexpected error.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Check server logs and handle exceptions gracefully.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-timeout">
            <i class="bi bi-clock-history"></i>
            <h5>Timeout</h5>
            <p>Request took too long to complete.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Increase timeout or optimize server response.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="error-bubble status-dns">
            <i class="bi bi-diagram-3-fill"></i>
            <h5>DNS / Connection Error</h5>
            <p>Client could not reach the server.</p>
            <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Check network, DNS, or server availability.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pro-tips">
        <h3>💡 Pro Tips for Debugging APIs</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Use Postman or Insomnia for testing APIs visually.</li>
            <li>Enable detailed logging for both requests and responses.</li>
            <li>Document all status codes returned by your API.</li>
            <li>Implement retries with exponential backoff for transient failures.</li>
            <li>Keep an error map for quick reference during debugging.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</div>

